    "The voice asked."
    "I do." 
    "replied brave Lucy."
    "She followed the voice that talked behind the stone wall."
    "The voice was barely audible."
    "Sometimes, Lucy had to press her ear on the wall to hear it again."
    "It scared her sometimes because the stone wall was warm, like the creature breathed so close to the stone."
    "Where are you?" 
    "Lucy would ask, and the voice would reply a mile away and Lucy would follow it until she could feel a warm patch on the stone wall."
    "Bet you can't see me." 
    "It said again."
